MATT: "Scanlan Shorthalt.
All right, come soon."

2094
01:35:42,000 --> 01:35:44,000
SAM: See you soon.

2095
01:35:44,000 --> 01:35:47,000
TRAVIS: Can I hit my head
on the doorway on the way out?

2096
01:35:47,000 --> 01:35:50,000
MATT: (shoomp)
LAURA AND MARISHA: (laugh)

2097
01:35:50,000 --> 01:35:52,000
MATT: (creak) You have to
kind of pull it out.

2098
01:35:52,000 --> 01:35:53,500
Yeah. You leave a nice big groove.

2099
01:35:53,500 --> 01:35:55,000
TRAVIS: It is nice, right?
MATT: Yeah.

2100
01:35:55,000 --> 01:35:56,800
TRAVIS: Okay, good.

2101
01:35:56,800 --> 01:36:00,500
MATT: (laughs) All right,
eventually you all gather again

2102
01:36:00,500 --> 01:36:06,000
back at the hall of the Slayer's Take.

2103
01:36:06,000 --> 01:36:09,000
You guys have just settled in

2104
01:36:09,000 --> 01:36:13,190
and are free to continue
any discussion you like

2105
01:36:13,190 --> 01:36:19,000
as you see Scanlan and Grog come in.

2106
01:36:19,000 --> 01:36:22,620
Say, you've since retrieved your hat

2107
01:36:22,620 --> 01:36:26,000
with your various
wonderfully-crafted accoutrements.

2108
01:36:26,000 --> 01:36:29,000
TRAVIS: 'Sup, bitches.
LAURA: Wow.

2109
01:36:29,000 --> 01:36:30,500
SAM: Look at that.
ASHLEY: Whoa.

2110
01:36:30,500 --> 01:36:32,000
TRAVIS: What happened?
SAM: Look at that.

2111
01:36:32,000 --> 01:36:34,000
ASHLEY: (gasps) Ohh...
TRAVIS: I know, right? Wait for it.

2112
01:36:34,000 --> 01:36:36,000
LIAM: (laughs)

2113
01:36:36,000 --> 01:36:41,000
LAURA: Whoa. Grog, you're so monstrous.
ASHLEY: What? Grog, that is so scary.

2114
01:36:41,000 --> 01:36:42,500
MARISHA: That's like
another 12 inches to you.

2115
01:36:42,500 --> 01:36:44,000
TRAVIS: I know.
MARISHA: You look so tall.

2116
01:36:44,000 --> 01:36:47,000
TRAVIS: It, like, changes
my whole battle strategy.

2117
01:36:47,000 --> 01:36:49,450
I'm now literally
the point of the spear.

2118
01:36:49,450 --> 01:36:54,050
ASHLEY: (gasps) You're so scary.
TALIESIN: How have we lived with this idiot?

2119
01:36:54,050 --> 01:36:57,100
TRAVIS: (laughs) I'm a sea monster!
ASHLEY: (roars)

2120
01:36:57,100 --> 01:37:00,160
TRAVIS: I'm like
the most wicked narwhal of all time!

2121
01:37:00,160 --> 01:37:02,600
Give me a pool! (laughs)

2122
01:37:02,600 --> 01:37:05,000
ASHLEY: Can I try it on?
TRAVIS: Yeah, you want to?

2123
01:37:05,000 --> 01:37:07,000
TRAVIS: (laughing)
I put it on Pike's head.

2124
01:37:07,000 --> 01:37:08,830
ASHLEY: Whoa, it's so heavy.

2125
01:37:08,830 --> 01:37:11,790
(all but Taliesin laugh)
TALIESIN: What is the world coming to?

2126
01:37:11,790 --> 01:37:13,220
TRAVIS: Is it as tall as she is?

2127
01:37:13,220 --> 01:37:16,000
MATT: You can see
the bottom of her mouth.

2128
01:37:16,000 --> 01:37:18,000
ASHLEY: Oh, Grog.

2129
01:37:18,000 --> 01:37:20,000
TRAVIS: Oh, yeah, look.

2130
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:23,000
Wait, turn around 180 degrees
and then run as fast as you can.

2131
01:37:23,000 --> 01:37:25,000
MARISHA: Oh, yeah, go!
Go! Go! Go, Pike! Go, go!

2132
01:37:25,000 --> 01:37:27,000
LAURA: (clapping) Go, Pike!
Go, Pike! Go, Pike!

2133
01:37:27,000 --> 01:37:29,000
MATT: Okay, make a perception check.

2134
01:37:29,000 --> 01:37:33,310
TALIESIN: (groans)
EVERYONE ELSE: (laughs)

2135
01:37:36,510 --> 01:37:38,000
ASHLEY: 9.

2136
01:37:38,000 --> 01:37:40,000
MATT: 9. You go running
straight out of the door--

2137
01:37:40,000 --> 01:37:41,500
LAURA: No!

2138
01:37:41,500 --> 01:37:43,620
MATT: You guys are like,
"Oh. No, Pike!"

2139
01:37:43,620 --> 01:37:46,000
She's already out the door,
over the stairs

2140
01:37:46,000 --> 01:37:48,000
(repeated thuds),
outside of the hall.

2141
01:37:48,000 --> 01:37:49,500
(sounds of dismay)

2142
01:37:49,500 --> 01:37:51,500
TRAVIS and LAURA: Oh no!

2143
01:37:51,500 --> 01:37:53,000
ASHLEY: I'm okay!

2144
01:37:53,000 --> 01:37:54,500
MATT: You guys rush out to go catch her

2145
01:37:54,500 --> 01:37:57,130
and the helmet is actually
embedded partway into the ground

2146
01:37:57,130 --> 01:37:58,770
and she's kind of--

2147
01:37:58,770 --> 01:38:00,000
MARISHA: Yeah!

2148
01:38:00,000 --> 01:38:04,000
MATT: And she's just laughing.

2149
01:38:04,000 --> 01:38:06,000
ASHLEY: (laughing) Grog,
get me out of this helmet.

2150
01:38:06,000 --> 01:38:08,000
TRAVIS: I pick her up by the feet.

2151
01:38:08,000 --> 01:38:10,470
TRAVIS: That was excellent. (giggles)

2152
01:38:10,470 --> 01:38:13,850
ASHLEY: As he's holding me up like that
I try to stab him with it.

2153
01:38:15,710 --> 01:38:19,000
TRAVIS: I yank it off of her head
and put her back on the ground.

2154
01:38:19,000 --> 01:38:21,230
LIAM: Vax has been
laughing hysterically,

2155
01:38:21,230 --> 01:38:24,000
giggle fits,
clutching his ribs the entire time.

2156
01:38:24,000 --> 01:38:27,000
And then is there
any of the staff here?

2157
01:38:27,000 --> 01:38:29,000
Anyone that's here? Anyone else?

2158
01:38:29,000 --> 01:38:33,000
MATT: You haven't seen Mertin.
Vanessa doesn't seem to have left.

2159
01:38:33,000 --> 01:38:34,500
LIAM: What about underlings?

2160
01:38:34,500 --> 01:38:36,000
MATT: I mean, there are

2161
01:38:36,000 --> 01:38:37,500
a few individuals here
that are part of the guildhall.

2162
01:38:37,500 --> 01:38:41,000
The hierarchy here
is more like the few that run it,

2163
01:38:41,000 --> 01:38:43,000
and then everyone else
comes and goes as they please.

2164
01:38:43,000 --> 01:38:45,580
LIAM: Yeah, yeah, come here, you.
Do you have a tub?

2165
01:38:45,580 --> 01:38:48,660
Do you have a bath? Look at me.
Do you have a bath? I need a bath.

2166
01:38:48,660 --> 01:38:50,000
MATT: "You look pretty rough."

2167
01:38:50,000 --> 01:38:51,000
LIAM: Yeah?

2168
01:38:51,000 --> 01:38:52,500
MATT: "Yeah. We could--

2169
01:38:52,500 --> 01:38:54,720
"we got a washroom in the back,
if you need it."

2170
01:38:54,720 --> 01:38:58,000
LIAM: Is it hot?
I feel like I need it to be hot.

2171
01:38:58,000 --> 01:39:00,000
MATT: "You get what you get. 
It's water, buddy."

2172
01:39:00,000 --> 01:39:01,500
LIAM: Okay.
That's perfect, thank you.

2173
01:39:01,500 --> 01:39:03,000
Grog, put that hat on again.

2174
01:39:03,000 --> 01:39:08,000
TRAVIS: Oh, yeah, hold on. (foomp)
LIAM: (laughs hysterically)

2175
01:39:08,000 --> 01:39:09,500
LIAM: All the way down the hall
to take a bath.

2176
01:39:09,500 --> 01:39:11,000
SAM: It's crazy. Did you guys
get him drunk or something?

2177
01:39:11,000 --> 01:39:12,500
TALIESIN: I don't know
what you people did, but...

2178
01:39:12,500 --> 01:39:14,000
ASHLEY: Well, he just...

2179
01:39:14,000 --> 01:39:15,500
TRAVIS: People respond to fear differently.

2180
01:39:15,500 --> 01:39:17,000
SAM: I guess so.
LAURA: He's gone insane.

2181
01:39:17,000 --> 01:39:18,500
MARISHA: He might have saw
the face of a god.

2182
01:39:18,500 --> 01:39:21,920
SAM: Whatever.
TRAVIS: He did?

2183
01:39:21,920 --> 01:39:23,470
MARISHA: Yeah.

2184
01:39:23,470 --> 01:39:25,500
ASHLEY: Yeah. The head of--

2185
01:39:25,500 --> 01:39:28,000
TRAVIS: By the way,
why is he covered in bloodbath?

2186
01:39:28,000 --> 01:39:30,000
ASHLEY: I think that was part of the--

2187
01:39:30,000 --> 01:39:32,000
MARISHA: Ritual? Communion?

2188
01:39:32,000 --> 01:39:35,000
ASHLEY: Getting to know his new god.

2189
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:37,000
TRAVIS: Did he kill a lot of people?

2190
01:39:37,000 --> 01:39:38,500
ASHLEY: Maybe he had to. I don't know.

2191
01:39:38,500 --> 01:39:40,000
TRAVIS: He did?
LAURA: So many, Grog.

2192
01:39:40,000 --> 01:39:42,500
TRAVIS: Oh my god.
LAURA: Yeah. It was a giant battle.

2193
01:39:42,500 --> 01:39:44,300
TRAVIS: Like, how many on two hands?

2194
01:39:44,300 --> 01:39:47,140
LAURA: Like at least this many.

2195
01:39:47,140 --> 01:39:51,000
TRAVIS: That's a legendary amount.
LAURA: That's more than six.

2196
01:39:51,000 --> 01:39:52,200
LAURA: I know.
ASHLEY: Yeah.

2197
01:39:52,200 --> 01:39:55,000
LIAM: Somewhere deep in the building,
far away:

2198
01:39:55,000 --> 01:40:00,000
LIAM: This is not hot!

2199
01:40:00,000 --> 01:40:02,000
MATT: The gruff individual chuckles.

2200
01:40:02,000 --> 01:40:05,000
"Heh. It never is."

2201
01:40:07,500 --> 01:40:09,000
I need you to make a tinkering check.

2202
01:40:09,000 --> 01:40:10,000
TALIESIN: Okay.

2203
01:40:10,000 --> 01:40:13,000
I'm sitting with my tea and my tools,
trying to ignore these people.

2204
01:40:13,000 --> 01:40:15,060
LAURA: Can I heat water up
in the fireplace?

2205
01:40:15,060 --> 01:40:16,620
MATT: Yeah, yeah,
it'll take you a little while.

2206
01:40:16,620 --> 01:40:19,000
TALIESIN: Please don't explode.

2207
01:40:19,000 --> 01:40:21,000
SAM: When I delivered
the materials to him--

2208
01:40:21,000 --> 01:40:24,000
TALIESIN: Oh, Jesus H. Fucking Christ.
MARISHA: Oh no, Taliesin...

2209
01:40:24,000 --> 01:40:26,000
SAM: Could I have inspired him at all,
when I delivered the materials?

2210
01:40:26,000 --> 01:40:27,500
TALIESIN: Please.
MATT: Sure.

2211
01:40:27,500 --> 01:40:30,000
SAM: All right.
MARISHA: Please inspire.

2212
01:40:30,000 --> 01:40:33,320
SAM: I will inspire--
oh my god, it's not even worth it.

2213
01:40:33,320 --> 01:40:36,750
TALIESIN: (muffled) Please inspire.
Do it. Do it, you bloody gnome!

2214
01:40:36,750 --> 01:40:38,460
SAM: Okay.
So when I delivered everything,

2215
01:40:38,460 --> 01:40:42,000
I just sang him a little song
to inspire him. And I sang,

2216
01:40:42,000 --> 01:40:46,000
SAM: (singing) 
Percy's gun, won't you come

2217
01:40:46,000 --> 01:40:49,630
and kill up all the dragons?

2218
01:40:49,630 --> 01:40:55,500
(others join in) Percy's gun,
won't you come, won't you come?

2219
01:40:55,500 --> 01:40:57,000
ASHLEY AND LIAM: Percy's gun!

2220
01:40:57,000 --> 01:40:59,000
(laughter)

2221
01:40:59,000 --> 01:41:01,000
MATT: Oh my god.
All right, take your d10.

2222
01:41:01,000 --> 01:41:02,500
LAURA: Ten! Ten! Ten!
LIAM: Do it! Do it!

2223
01:41:02,500 --> 01:41:04,000
MARISHA: Oh my god, it's a 10!
TALIESIN: Better!

2224
01:41:04,000 --> 01:41:05,500
SAM: That was a 10.
TALIESIN: Thank you.

2225
01:41:05,500 --> 01:41:07,000
MARISHA: I get excited. Sorry.
LIAM: Pretty good song.

2226
01:41:07,000 --> 01:41:09,500
TALIESIN: Proficiency,
tinkering, plus the--

2227
01:41:09,500 --> 01:41:11,000
MATT: Well, your proficiency
is what you get with the roll

2228
01:41:11,000 --> 01:41:12,000
and then it's your dex bonus.

2229
01:41:12,000 --> 01:41:17,000
TALIESIN: Okay, so proficiency,
dex, okay, thank you, god.

2230
01:41:17,000 --> 01:41:19,000
TALIESIN: (muttering) That's 11...
LIAM: (hums Black Hole Sun)

2231
01:41:19,000 --> 01:41:21,000
TALIESIN: 23.
MATT: 23. What did you roll naturally?

2232
01:41:21,000 --> 01:41:22,500
SAM: A 2.
TALIESIN: 2.

2233
01:41:22,500 --> 01:41:24,000
LIAM: (laughs)
LAURA: Whoa.

2234
01:41:24,000 --> 01:41:25,860
SAM: Plus 10.
MATT: Ah.

2235
01:41:25,860 --> 01:41:27,000
TALIESIN AND MARISHA: Plus 10.

2236
01:41:27,000 --> 01:41:29,000
TALIESIN: Made it 12.
MATT: Wow. All righty.

2237
01:41:29,000 --> 01:41:31,000
TALIESIN: It's not complicated,
but I've got a good design,

2238
01:41:31,000 --> 01:41:34,000
and it has two nifty things.

2239
01:41:34,000 --> 01:41:35,500
MATT: What are the nifty things?

2240
01:41:35,500 --> 01:41:37,000
SAM: Fingers.

2241
01:41:37,000 --> 01:41:38,500
TALIESIN: It doesn't actually
have fingers.

2242
01:41:38,500 --> 01:41:42,000
It's a mitt piece, strap-on,

2243
01:41:42,000 --> 01:41:45,000
it can lock the thumb
and lock the hand

2244
01:41:45,000 --> 01:41:47,000
so you can open it, lock,
close it, lock.

2245
01:41:47,000 --> 01:41:49,000
It's got little flip-locks.

2246
01:41:49,000 --> 01:41:50,000
MATT: Mm-hm.

2247
01:41:50,000 --> 01:41:52,000
TALIESIN: You can detach the hand

2248
01:41:52,000 --> 01:41:54,690
and put a pick spike on
for mining. Like a mining punch.

2249
01:41:54,690 --> 01:41:56,320
LIAM: Is it like Young Frankenstein?

2250
01:41:56,320 --> 01:41:58,000
(mechanical sound effects)

2251
01:41:58,000 --> 01:42:02,500
TALIESIN: It's more Dustin Hoffman "Hook",
but, you know.

2252
01:42:02,500 --> 01:42:04,000
MARISHA: Oh, sure.
LAURA: Oh, that's nice.

2253
01:42:04,000 --> 01:42:05,500
MARISHA: I was thinking
Go-Go-Gadget Finger.

2254
01:42:05,500 --> 01:42:07,000
TALIESIN: Because it's got
the click, pull, click.

2255
01:42:07,000 --> 01:42:10,000
MATT: Right.

2256
01:42:10,000 --> 01:42:11,500
TALIESIN: I can do it
with all these things.

2257
01:42:11,500 --> 01:42:13,000
I can graph it. So.

2258
01:42:13,000 --> 01:42:14,000
MATT: (laughs)

2259
01:42:14,000 --> 01:42:16,000
TALIESIN: Reasonable.
It's not pretty.

2260
01:42:16,000 --> 01:42:17,500
MATT: It takes you a few hours

2261
01:42:17,500 --> 01:42:19,000
and gets you into
the early parts of the evening,

2262
01:42:19,000 --> 01:42:25,000
but you do manage
to go ahead and complete it.

2263
01:42:25,000 --> 01:42:28,000
You manage to get it finished up

2264
01:42:28,000 --> 01:42:31,000
and you're pretty proud of your work,
actually, and you feel--

2265
01:42:31,000 --> 01:42:33,450
the whistle you're still doing
as you do the final bits,

2266
01:42:33,450 --> 01:42:35,000
you realize is the song
that Scanlan sang for you,

2267
01:42:35,000 --> 01:42:36,500
just looping in your head.

2268
01:42:36,500 --> 01:42:38,000
It happened to push you
through your work

2269
01:42:38,000 --> 01:42:40,500
and get your final piece completed.

2270
01:42:40,500 --> 01:42:42,320
TALIESIN: I also carved
a little message inside

2271
01:42:42,320 --> 01:42:45,000
that will not matter
unless it actually becomes pertinent.

2272
01:42:45,000 --> 01:42:48,000
MATT: Okay.

2273
01:42:48,000 --> 01:42:49,780
TALIESIN: You don't get to know
until you ask offscreen.

2274
01:42:49,780 --> 01:42:50,970
SAM: You don't know.
LAURA: (laughs) Ohhh.

2275
01:42:50,970 --> 01:42:52,170
MATT: Okay. I'm excited. Okay.

2276
01:42:52,170 --> 01:42:53,820
MARISHA: That's right, DM.
TRAVIS: That never happens.

2277
01:42:53,820 --> 01:42:58,100
MATT: (laughs) Try me. Okay.
Do you go and deliver it?

2278
01:42:58,100 --> 01:42:59,920
TALIESIN: I do go and deliver it.

2279
01:42:59,920 --> 01:43:03,000
MATT: Okay.
As the sun begins to set in Vasselheim,

2280
01:43:03,000 --> 01:43:05,910
you make your way back over
to the Braving Grounds,

2281
01:43:05,910 --> 01:43:11,000
which as you look across, too,
as the night goes dark,

2282
01:43:11,000 --> 01:43:13,420
the Braving Grounds itself
has a whole different life to it.

2283
01:43:13,420 --> 01:43:18,020
There are so many forges
and smelters going that there's--

2284
01:43:18,020 --> 01:43:20,200
most buildings have
this bright orange glow

2285
01:43:20,200 --> 01:43:22,190
through the ceiling
and these various openings

2286
01:43:22,190 --> 01:43:25,000
where fumes and smoke and exhaust
are sent up

2287
01:43:25,000 --> 01:43:29,000
from the various
production constructs and such.

2288
01:43:29,000 --> 01:43:32,000
It has this very luminescent look
in comparison to a lot of the city.

2289
01:43:32,000 --> 01:43:33,190
It's very interesting.

2290
01:43:33,190 --> 01:43:36,000
It reminds you of the deep,
deep portions of Kraghammer,

2291
01:43:36,000 --> 01:43:41,000
where most of
the actual fire and melted rock

2292
01:43:41,000 --> 01:43:45,000
was being smelted
and gathered and heated.

2293
01:43:45,000 --> 01:43:47,000
So you make your way to the hovel.

2294
01:43:47,000 --> 01:43:50,410
The roof workers are no longer there,
and the door is closed.

2295
01:43:53,380 --> 01:43:58,000
TALIESIN: (knocks) Victor?
I've got your hand.

2296
01:43:59,600 --> 01:44:02,000
MATT: "(muffled) I'm sleeping."

2297
01:44:02,000 --> 01:44:04,000
TALIESIN: Do you want your hand?

2298
01:44:04,000 --> 01:44:06,000
MATT: "(muffled) You want me to sleep?"

2299
01:44:08,000 --> 01:44:10,270
TALIESIN: I don't see why
they're mutually exclusive.

2300
01:44:10,270 --> 01:44:12,000
MARISHA: (laughs)

2301
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:14,000
MATT: You hear (scraping sound)
a bunch of different locks fiddling.

2302
01:44:14,000 --> 01:44:16,000
(series of clicks) (fwoosh)

2303
01:44:16,000 --> 01:44:18,000
And the door opens
and you see Victor,

2304
01:44:18,000 --> 01:44:20,000
clean-faced for the first time
you've really seen him before,

2305
01:44:20,000 --> 01:44:22,000
and he has a nightcap

2306
01:44:22,000 --> 01:44:23,500
which sort of (foomf)
in front of his face,

2307
01:44:23,500 --> 01:44:25,000
with a little puffball at the end.

2308
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:26,000
He's like,

2309
01:44:26,000 --> 01:44:29,010
"I told you.
I was trying-- oh! Hey.

2310
01:44:29,010 --> 01:44:32,000
"(hesitantly) Percival?"

2311
01:44:32,000 --> 01:44:34,590
TALIESIN: Yes, that's quite good.
I love your hat.

2312
01:44:34,590 --> 01:44:36,500
MATT: "Thank you.
It's comfy to sleep in."

2313
01:44:36,500 --> 01:44:38,330
TALIESIN: It looks it.
MATT: "Did you bring my hand?"

2314
01:44:38,330 --> 01:44:40,860
TALIESIN: I did. I grabbed your hand
