01:46:07,000 --> 01:46:08,500
still holding the kettle
and splashing everywhere,

2353
01:46:08,500 --> 01:46:11,000
and he's flipping through cabinets
and knocking pieces of glass out.

2354
01:46:11,000 --> 01:46:13,000
"Ah! Found it."

2355
01:46:13,000 --> 01:46:15,000
Pulls out another little ceramic cup

2356
01:46:15,000 --> 01:46:22,000
and pours the tea in,
sets it down. (chink, click)

2357
01:46:22,000 --> 01:46:24,000
"(cackles)"

2358
01:46:24,000 --> 01:46:27,000
SAM: (laughs)

2359
01:46:27,000 --> 01:46:30,000
MATT: "To new hands!"
TALIESIN: To new hands.

2360
01:46:30,000 --> 01:46:32,000
SAM: That's a great toast.

2361
01:46:32,000 --> 01:46:35,000
MATT: It is pungent. It is bitter.

2362
01:46:35,000 --> 01:46:38,000
MATT: It has been steeped way too long.
ASHLEY: Gunpowder tea.

2363
01:46:38,000 --> 01:46:41,000
MATT: But it definitely
cleans out the sinuses.

2364
01:46:41,000 --> 01:46:44,290
And there is a hint of gunpowder
to the flavoring.

2365
01:46:44,290 --> 01:46:46,500
You get the sense
that pretty much everything in this room

2366
01:46:46,500 --> 01:46:48,000
is marinated in some way,
shape, or form

2367
01:46:48,000 --> 01:46:50,500
to be flammable.

2368
01:46:50,500 --> 01:46:52,000
TALIESIN: (hoarsely) Victor.

2369
01:46:52,000 --> 01:46:54,000
(laughter)

2370
01:46:54,000 --> 01:46:56,000
MATT: "It can put hair on your balls."

2371
01:46:56,000 --> 01:47:00,000
TALIESIN: Ohhh, probably.

2372
01:47:00,000 --> 01:47:05,000
Has a woman been by
to buy black powder?

2373
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:09,000
(coughs) Has a woman been by?

