I don't really like the ocean.

4116
03:23:42,490 --> 03:23:44,500
(laughter)

4117
03:23:44,500 --> 03:23:46,000
MATT: You guys all going to rest?

4118
03:23:46,000 --> 03:23:47,500
MARISHA: I have one thing I'd like to do.

4119
03:23:47,500 --> 03:23:49,000
MATT: Okay, what do you want to do?

4120
03:23:49,000 --> 03:23:51,000
MARISHA: I want to go back

4121
03:23:51,000 --> 03:23:53,500
to our little cave that we dug out
under where the Sun Tree is.

4122
03:23:53,500 --> 03:23:55,000
Is that still there?

4123
03:23:55,000 --> 03:23:56,500
MATT: Yeah, it's still there.

4124
03:23:56,500 --> 03:23:58,000
MARISHA: I want to go there,

4125
03:23:58,000 --> 03:24:01,000
and I want to kind of sit down
and meditate for a second.

4126
03:24:01,000 --> 03:24:07,000
And I want to cast Speak With Plants

4127
03:24:07,000 --> 03:24:11,000
and have a little chat
with the Sun Tree.

4128
03:24:11,000 --> 03:24:14,000
MATT: Okay. (laughs)
You cast the spell,

4129
03:24:14,000 --> 03:24:16,000
you reach out
and touch the roots of the tree,

4130
03:24:16,000 --> 03:24:18,230
the roots of which have more color
than they did before.

4131
03:24:18,230 --> 03:24:22,000
The dull gray has become
more of a full brown.

4132
03:24:22,000 --> 03:24:26,000
The earth here smells of fresh,
damp earth.

4133
03:24:26,000 --> 03:24:28,900
The tree, while still
in the winter phase,

4134
03:24:28,900 --> 03:24:34,000
is definitely teeming with life,
to where it once didn't.

4135
03:24:34,000 --> 03:24:36,000
MARISHA: I reach out
and I touch the roots.

4136
03:24:36,000 --> 03:24:41,000
Can I just kind of feel,
sense the arcane ley-lines

4137
03:24:41,000 --> 03:24:46,000
that Allura was talking about
that the tree's in the center of?

4138
03:24:46,000 --> 03:24:51,000
MATT: Mmm... not really.

4139
03:24:51,000 --> 03:24:56,550
In speaking to the tree,
you can ask questions,

4140
03:24:56,550 --> 03:25:00,000
but you're not quite--

4141
03:25:00,000 --> 03:25:02,000
you find yourself unable
to tune into that

4142
03:25:02,000 --> 03:25:06,000
or tap into that source of magic.

4143
03:25:06,000 --> 03:25:08,000
At this place, at least.

4144
03:25:08,000 --> 03:25:12,530
MARISHA: Okay. So I just reach out,
touch the tree, and say,

4145
03:25:12,530 --> 03:25:17,780
"Hey, old friend.

4146
03:25:17,780 --> 03:25:22,000
"How are you feeling? Doing better?"

4147
03:25:22,000 --> 03:25:25,080
MATT: "Hey, bud. Much better."

4148
03:25:25,080 --> 03:25:27,000
(laughter)

4149
03:25:27,000 --> 03:25:29,000
MARISHA: You're pretty cool, Sun Tree.

4150
03:25:29,000 --> 03:25:30,500
MATT: "Sun Tree, A-OK."

4151
03:25:30,500 --> 03:25:37,000
(laughter)

4152
03:25:37,000 --> 03:25:39,000
MARISHA: Hey, Sun Tree?

4153
03:25:39,000 --> 03:25:44,000
MATT: "Yeah?"

4154
03:25:44,000 --> 03:25:47,000
MARISHA: I was just wondering
if you knew--

4155
03:25:47,000 --> 03:25:49,000
if you could tell me anything
about this

4156
03:25:49,000 --> 03:25:51,000
terrible cancerous tree
in the Feywild,

4157
03:25:51,000 --> 03:25:52,500
if you knew anything about it?

4158
03:25:52,500 --> 03:25:54,000
He might be like
your brother or something.

4159
03:25:54,000 --> 03:25:55,500
MATT: "Tree cancer? What?"

4160
03:25:55,500 --> 03:25:57,000
MARISHA: No! No, okay.

4161
03:25:57,000 --> 03:26:01,000
There's this tree in the Feywild
and it might have

4162
03:26:01,000 --> 03:26:05,000
a man living in it
called Fenthras.

4163
03:26:05,000 --> 03:26:06,500
TRAVIS: (quietly) The bow.

4164
03:26:06,500 --> 03:26:08,630
MARISHA: No, sorry,
that's the name of the bow,

4165
03:26:08,630 --> 03:26:14,000
the bow is in it, named Fenthras,
and it might be a really sick tree.

4166
03:26:14,000 --> 03:26:17,020
Can you tell me where there's
a really sick tree, maybe in the Feywild?

4167
03:26:17,020 --> 03:26:19,000
MATT: "That sounds sad, but no.

4168
03:26:19,000 --> 03:26:21,000
"I don't know
a tree like that, sorry.

4169
03:26:21,000 --> 03:26:23,000
"I've been here in Whitestone
since day one."

4170
03:26:23,000 --> 03:26:26,000
(laughter)

4171
03:26:26,000 --> 03:26:30,000
LIAM: Want to play hacky sack?
TALIESIN: Born and raised.

4172
03:26:30,000 --> 03:26:32,810
MATT: So I graduated from Berkeley
and made my way to Whitestone.

4173
03:26:32,810 --> 03:26:34,000
(laughter)

4174
03:26:34,000 --> 03:26:35,960
TRAVIS: My twigs smoke the doob.

4175
03:26:35,960 --> 03:26:38,000
SAM: "Barkeley."
MARISHA: "Barkeley!"

4176
03:26:38,000 --> 03:26:39,500
ASHLEY: Put a pair of Birkenstocks
on its branches.

4177
03:26:39,500 --> 03:26:41,000
TRAVIS: "Birkenstalks."
MATT: (groans)

4178
03:26:41,000 --> 03:26:42,820
LAURA: "Birkenstalks?" I like it.

4179
03:26:42,820 --> 03:26:44,380
MARISHA: Hey, Sun Tree?

4180
03:26:44,380 --> 03:26:46,220
MATT: "Yeah?"

4181
03:26:49,000 --> 03:26:51,000
MARISHA: You apparently kind of live

4182
03:26:51,000 --> 03:26:55,000
in the middle of all these
arcane ley-lines of the world.

4183
03:26:55,000 --> 03:26:57,500
MATT: "Yeah."
TALIESIN: (cracks up)

4184
03:26:57,500 --> 03:26:59,000
MARISHA: How far do those stretch?

4185
03:26:59,000 --> 03:27:03,000
MATT: "Long way, Kiki.

4186
03:27:03,000 --> 03:27:07,000
"Long way."

4187
03:27:07,000 --> 03:27:10,000
(laughter)

4188
03:27:10,000 --> 03:27:12,500
MARISHA: Can you kind of give me
a rough idea?

4189
03:27:12,500 --> 03:27:14,830
Do they go
to the other side of the world?

4190
03:27:14,830 --> 03:27:18,000
Can you stretch all over the world?

4191
03:27:18,000 --> 03:27:22,000
MATT: "Nah, just right here.
Pelor put me here for a reason."

4192
03:27:22,000 --> 03:27:25,000
MARISHA: Who? Pelor?
MATT: "Yeah."

4193
03:27:25,000 --> 03:27:27,000
MARISHA: Right.

4194
03:27:27,000 --> 03:27:31,100
So you're not a natural tree,
you're a tree from the gods?

4195
03:27:32,550 --> 03:27:33,880
MATT: "Sure."

4196
03:27:35,000 --> 03:27:38,000
MARISHA: All right.

4197
03:27:38,000 --> 03:27:40,740
Well, anyway,
you're really awesome, Sun Tree.

4198
03:27:40,740 --> 03:27:42,670
MATT: "Speak for yourself, Kiki."

4199
03:27:42,670 --> 03:27:46,000
MARISHA: Yeah, you're so cool.

4200
03:27:46,000 --> 03:27:48,000
Okay, so it was good talking to you.

4201
03:27:48,000 --> 03:27:49,980
MATT: "You, too."

4202
03:27:51,170 --> 03:27:54,000
MARISHA: I'll walk through you soon.
Okay, bye.

4203
03:27:54,000 --> 03:27:56,000
MATT: (laughs)

4204
03:27:56,000 --> 03:27:57,500
MARISHA: And then I leave.
MATT: All right.

4205
03:27:57,500 --> 03:28:00,830
LAURA: I want to make a once-over on Vax
and make sure that--

4206
03:28:00,830 --> 03:28:02,800
So you did,
you got all the blood off, then?

4207
03:28:02,800 --> 03:28:04,200
LIAM: What are you doing?
Yeah, I took a bath.

4208
03:28:04,200 --> 03:28:05,500
LAURA: I mean,
we got all cleaned up for tonight.

4209
03:28:05,500 --> 03:28:07,000
I just want to make sure
you didn't ruin it

4210
03:28:07,000 --> 03:28:09,000
by keeping some of the blood
in your freaking hair.

4211
03:28:09,000 --> 03:28:11,440
LIAM: Don't I look all right?
I'm fine! What's your problem?

4212
03:28:11,440 --> 03:28:13,830
LAURA: Nothing! Just making sure
you're doing all right.

4213
03:28:13,830 --> 03:28:15,000
LIAM: Yeah.
LAURA: All the blood's gone.

4214
03:28:15,000 --> 03:28:17,000
LIAM: Yeah. It's all gone.
LAURA: You're great.

4215
03:28:17,000 --> 03:28:19,000
LIAM: I'm doing much better.
LAURA: Good.

4216
03:28:19,000 --> 03:28:22,000
LIAM: Much better.

4217
03:28:22,000 --> 03:28:23,500
You ready for the Feywild?

4218
03:28:23,500 --> 03:28:28,000
LAURA: Fuck, no, not ready,
but we can do it.

4219
03:28:28,000 --> 03:28:29,420
LIAM: Oh.

4220
03:28:32,000 --> 03:28:34,000
TALIESIN: Stupid to settle.
MARISHA: (snorts)

4221
03:28:34,000 --> 03:28:35,500
LAURA: I walk over to Percy.

4222
03:28:35,500 --> 03:28:37,000
TALIESIN: I was about
to walk out the door,

4223
03:28:37,000 --> 03:28:39,000
but if you're walking--

4224
03:28:39,000 --> 03:28:42,000
LAURA: Before you leave,
I whisper in your ear,

4225
03:28:42,000 --> 03:28:44,000
"You still have
a little blood behind your ear."

4226
03:28:44,000 --> 03:28:45,000
TRAVIS: (gasps)

4227
03:28:45,000 --> 03:28:47,630
TALIESIN: Do you want 
to take a walk with me?

4228
03:28:47,630 --> 03:28:53,000
LAURA: (sighs) Sure.

4229
03:28:53,000 --> 03:28:55,000
TALIESIN: We take a very quiet walk
around Whitestone.

4230
03:28:55,000 --> 03:28:56,500
I want to pass all of the temples

4231
03:28:56,500 --> 03:29:01,000
that are either
still standing or destroyed.

4232
03:29:01,000 --> 03:29:03,000
I just want to take a temple tour.

4233
03:29:03,000 --> 03:29:05,980
Not stopping, not talking,
I just want to see what they look like.

4234
03:29:05,980 --> 03:29:10,000
Pelor looks good.
The one in the cemetery?

4235
03:29:10,000 --> 03:29:12,000
MATT: The one in the cemetery
is still under construction.

4236
03:29:12,000 --> 03:29:14,000
That one needs a little more work.

4237
03:29:14,000 --> 03:29:16,000
TALIESIN: While in the cemetery--

4238
03:29:16,000 --> 03:29:19,000
I assume that it's still a mess.

4239
03:29:19,000 --> 03:29:21,000
MATT: Most of the graves
have been refilled,

4240
03:29:21,000 --> 03:29:23,000
the corpses have been brought back.

4241
03:29:23,000 --> 03:29:27,000
Most of the dead that were brought forth
from the previous owners

4242
03:29:27,000 --> 03:29:28,500
have been returned.

4243
03:29:28,500 --> 03:29:30,000
That was one of the first
orders of business

4244
03:29:30,000 --> 03:29:32,000
that people who live here did,

4245
03:29:32,000 --> 03:29:34,000
was to return their families
to the earth.

4246
03:29:34,000 --> 03:29:37,400
TALIESIN: There were
a couple of lords' crypts in there.

4247
03:29:37,400 --> 03:29:41,000
Was there an Anders family crypt, 
at one point?

4248
03:29:41,000 --> 03:29:43,000
MATT: There would have been, yeah.

4249
03:29:43,000 --> 03:29:45,000
TALIESIN: Cool. All right.

4250
03:29:45,000 --> 03:29:47,460
I'm going to walk back to the castle,

4251
03:29:47,460 --> 03:29:50,000
with you in tow,
and I'm going to find Zahra.

4252
03:29:50,000 --> 03:29:53,000
MATT: Okay.

4253
03:29:53,000 --> 03:29:56,000
LAURA: Are you going to tell me
why you went and saw the Raven Queen?

4254
03:29:56,000 --> 03:29:57,500
TALIESIN: Yes. Come.

4255
03:29:57,500 --> 03:29:59,000
MATT: All right.

4256
03:29:59,000 --> 03:30:02,510
You come back to the study
where you originally found Zahra.

4257
03:30:02,510 --> 03:30:05,010
She's still there poring over books,
but is now half-asleep.

4258
03:30:05,010 --> 03:30:07,000
She has a little candle
that's starting to flicker out

4259
03:30:07,000 --> 03:30:10,000
and she has her feet up on the desk
and her tail's kind of curled up

4260
03:30:10,000 --> 03:30:13,000
and she's falling asleep
into the book as you walk in.

4261
03:30:13,000 --> 03:30:15,000
LAURA: (whispering) Dear--
MATT: "What?"

4262
03:30:15,000 --> 03:30:18,000
LAURA: We all need sleep sometimes, hon.

4263
03:30:18,000 --> 03:30:22,000
MATT: "Sleep's for the boring."

4264
03:30:22,000 --> 03:30:23,500
TALIESIN: I have a task for you,

4265
03:30:23,500 --> 03:30:30,000
if you have the time and energy
for something a bit quiet, but necessary.

4266
03:30:30,000 --> 03:30:32,000
MATT: "What do you ask, Percy?"

4267
03:30:32,000 --> 03:30:33,500
TALIESIN: I'm going to have
the deeds

4268
03:30:33,500 --> 03:30:38,000
to the Anders family crypt
transferred to your name.

4269
03:30:38,000 --> 03:30:40,000
I want you to clean it out.

4270
03:30:40,000 --> 03:30:43,000
Throw the bodies wherever;
he has disgraced himself.

4271
03:30:43,000 --> 03:30:46,000
Clean them.

4272
03:30:46,000 --> 03:30:48,000
And if you can,
if you can find people who can do it,

4273
03:30:48,000 --> 03:30:50,000
I want to very quietly,
in that crypt,

4274
03:30:50,000 --> 03:30:55,380
create a small shrine
to the Raven Queen.

4275
03:30:57,000 --> 03:30:58,500
This will help.

4276
03:30:58,500 --> 03:31:02,000
And I bring out
the vial of blood from the pit.

4277
03:31:02,000 --> 03:31:05,000
Perhaps they will know
what to do with that.

4278
03:31:05,000 --> 03:31:06,000
MATT: "Intriguing."

4279
03:31:06,000 --> 03:31:08,000
TALIESIN: But I would like her
to have a quiet mark in this city.

4280
03:31:08,000 --> 03:31:09,910
LAURA: Is this for you,
or for my brother?

4281
03:31:12,000 --> 03:31:16,000
TALIESIN: ...It's for your brother,
so that he can help us.

4282
03:31:16,000 --> 03:31:21,000
We're apparently all in this together.

4283
03:31:21,000 --> 03:31:23,560
LAURA: I give Percy a kiss on the cheek.

4284
03:31:23,560 --> 03:31:29,000
TALIESIN: Oh. Thank you.
MATT: "All right."

4285
03:31:29,000 --> 03:31:31,000
TALIESIN: We need all the help we can get.

4286
03:31:31,000 --> 03:31:34,000
MATT: "Very well.
I'm sure it can be done.

4287
03:31:34,000 --> 03:31:36,000
"I never owned a crypt before.
I'm excited."

4288
03:31:36,000 --> 03:31:38,000
LAURA: It's exciting. (laughs)

4289
03:31:38,000 --> 03:31:40,000
MATT: She takes the vial
and puts it on the table.

4290
03:31:40,000 --> 03:31:41,480
LAURA: I think it suits you.

4291
03:31:41,480 --> 03:31:45,000
TALIESIN: Tell anyone you'd like
where I went. It's not a secret.

4292
03:31:45,000 --> 03:31:47,510
I just wasn't ready to...

4293
03:31:50,000 --> 03:31:53,000
I don't think your brother--

4294
03:31:53,000 --> 03:31:55,000
I would hate for him
to think I'm competing.

4295
03:31:55,000 --> 03:31:57,500
I just had some questions.

4296
03:31:57,500 --> 03:31:59,000
LAURA: I won't tell anyone, Percy.

4297
03:31:59,000 --> 03:32:00,500
TALIESIN: Thank you.

4298
03:32:00,500 --> 03:32:02,000
LAURA: Your business is yours.

4299
03:32:02,000 --> 03:32:04,000
And mine, because I noticed. 
(chuckles)

4300
03:32:04,000 --> 03:32:05,000
MARISHA: (snorts)

4301
03:32:05,000 --> 03:32:09,000
TALIESIN: Thank you for noticing,
and... I'm trying hard

4302
03:32:09,000 --> 03:32:12,000
not to make it my business.

4303
03:32:12,000 --> 03:32:15,000
It's hard to remember sometimes.

4304
03:32:15,000 --> 03:32:18,000
TALIESIN: (sighs)
LAURA: (quietly) We're all family.

4305
03:32:18,000 --> 03:32:23,000
TALIESIN: That's awful, isn't it. 
(sighs)

4306
03:32:23,000 --> 03:32:25,000
I'm going to go to my room--

4307
03:32:25,000 --> 03:32:27,000
LAURA: Oh! Percy!
TALIESIN: Yes?

4308
03:32:27,000 --> 03:32:28,000
LAURA: Sorry.

4309
03:32:28,000 --> 03:32:30,000
If Zahra wanted to make
some dragon arrows,

4310
03:32:30,000 --> 03:32:33,000
could she use stuff here
in the castle?

4311
03:32:33,000 --> 03:32:35,390
TALIESIN: I'll talk to my sister
on the way out.

4312
03:32:35,390 --> 03:32:37,000
I'll write her a letter
and see if they can--

4313
03:32:37,000 --> 03:32:39,000
they may have to delve
into our materials for it,

4314
03:32:39,000 --> 03:32:41,000
but I think we're good.

4315
03:32:41,000 --> 03:32:42,000
LAURA: Yes.

4316
03:32:42,000 --> 03:32:45,000
TALIESIN: We'll talk about
using our materials for such a thing,

4317
03:32:45,000 --> 03:32:48,000
and I will talk to her about that.

4318
03:32:48,000 --> 03:32:50,000
LAURA: All right.

4319
03:32:50,000 --> 03:32:52,000
TALIESIN: I'm going to do
my little thing and if it works, great,

4320
03:32:52,000 --> 03:32:55,000
and if not,
we'll speak not of it for a while.

4321
03:32:55,000 --> 03:32:57,490
MATT: Okay. Go ahead
and make your tinkering check.

4322
03:33:00,000 --> 03:33:04,000
TALIESIN: Better! 30.

4323
03:33:04,000 --> 03:33:06,000
MATT: That'll do.

4324
03:33:06,000 --> 03:33:08,000
TALIESIN: I craft a brooch.

4325
03:33:08,000 --> 03:33:11,000
It's not even a brooch,
it's a clasp.

4326
03:33:11,000 --> 03:33:15,000
I had built these pieces of it
earlier on in the game.

4327
03:33:15,000 --> 03:33:17,000
For the last three weeks
I've been working on this.

4328
03:33:17,000 --> 03:33:20,000
I've taken the raven skull
that you gave me

4329
03:33:20,000 --> 03:33:22,000
and made a mold

4330
03:33:22,000 --> 03:33:25,000
and poured melted silver
into a bird skull,

4331
03:33:25,000 --> 03:33:26,500
a silver bird skull.

4332
03:33:26,500 --> 03:33:29,000
Taken a ruby and set it behind it,

4333
03:33:29,000 --> 03:33:33,000
built it into a clasp
that does not reflect,

4334
03:33:33,000 --> 03:33:38,000
and in it,
put a sachet of-- satchel...

4335
03:33:38,000 --> 03:33:40,000
MARISHA and LAURA: Sachet.

4336
03:33:40,000 --> 03:33:44,000
TALIESIN: Thank you. My brain? Coffee.

4337
03:33:44,000 --> 03:33:47,310
Of myrrh and--

4338
03:33:47,310 --> 03:33:49,000
SAM: Frankincense?

4339
03:33:49,000 --> 03:33:55,000
TALIESIN: (snorts and laughs)
Myrrh, sandalwood, opium,

4340
03:33:55,000 --> 03:33:58,000
and dragon's blood.

4341
03:33:58,000 --> 03:34:01,000
Not real dragon's blood,
but dragon's blood--

4342
03:34:01,000 --> 03:34:02,000
SAM: True blood.

4343
03:34:02,000 --> 03:34:04,000
TALIESIN: Sap. It's a sap.
It's a tree sap.

4344
03:34:04,000 --> 03:34:06,000
Put the whole thing together.

4345
03:34:06,000 --> 03:34:08,000
LIAM: You've had opium
